news.title: U.S. home builder sentiment hits seven-month low in April: NAHB
news.para: The housing market is under the spotlight as the Federal Reserve adopts an aggressive monetary policy stance in its fight against sky-high inflation, sending the 30-year fixed mortgage rate above 5% for first time in over a decade.

news.title: Turkey's house price index surges 96% annually in February
news.para: In the country's largest city Istanbul, home to around a fifth of Turkey's population of 85 million, the index climbed 106.3% on the year.

news.title: Max Ventures and Industries to amalgamate with subsidiary Max Estates
news.para: ​Its board had then authorised the Investment and Finance Committee to explore various modalities for restructuring with Max Estates Ltd and be renamed as Max Estates after receiving the required statutory approvals.

news.title: China developers speed up diversification after debt-led growth fuels crisis
news.para: KWG Group Holdings, CIFI Holdings and state-backed China Resources Land were among developers that listed diversification plans along with their recent financial results.

news.title: Builders fear non-completion of projects unless raw material costs are controlled
news.para: ​Releasing its report titled 'National Price Rise Impact Study 2022', Credai National President Harsh Vardhan Patodia said housing prices have increased 5-8 per cent due to rise in cost of construction and rates are expected to rise further by 5-7 per cent, taking the total increase to 10-15 per cent across India.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' sales bookings up 45% to Rs 1,739 crore in FY22
news.para: In terms of sales volumes, the company sold 2.71 million square feet in 2021-22 from 2.08 million square feet in the previous year. The average realisation increased 11 per cent to Rs 6,407 per square feet from Rs 5,785 per square feet.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh to spend Rs 13,000 crore on housing scheme
news.para: The chief minister also told the officials to construct storage points in the layouts given to the beneficiaries. He also told the officials to find alternative sites to be given as some of the layouts are in court disputes.

news.title: Ajmera Realty & Infra to launch six projects in next two financial years
news.para: The investment for all the six new projects will be funded through a mix of internal accruals, bank loans and advances from customers against sales.

news.title: Web portal launched to help citizens rectify land records in Jharkhand
news.para: Director of land acquisition and land archives, Jharkhand, Uma Shankar Singh told TOI that many could not benefit from the schemes under Jharbhoomi, a portal for online land registration, due to documentation errors.

news.title: Pune cantonment board starts process for revision of property tax
news.para: As per the Cantonment Act, 2006, the cantonment can revise the tax every three years. The last such revision took place for the period 2017-2020.

news.title: Civic bodies in Chhattisgarh to offer freehold over properties
news.para: In a review meeting of the urban administration and development department, environment and housing department, officials said that the online building permit system has been implemented for construction on residential plots up to 500 square meters in nine municipal corporations of the state.

news.title: Administration allows Chandigarh civic body to collect property tax from 13 villages
news.para: The civic body is all set to earn additional Rs 76.11 lakh from the 3,081 commercial properties falling in the villages.

news.title: Mysuru city corporation collects record property tax in two weeks
news.para: In the last two and half weeks, although there were extended weekends and festival holidays, Mysuru City Corporation collected Rs 21 crore in taxes — more than nearly 40% — mostly residential.

news.title: Over 13,700 applications for 415 plots near Jewar airport
news.para: ​​The authority had included in the draw plots ranging from 300 to 4,000 sq metres across sectors 16, 17, 18, 20 and 22D.

news.title: Patna HC directs ED to register case against builder
news.para: A single bench of Justice Sandeep Kumar, while hearing an anticipatory bail plea of one Prabhat Kumar Ranjan, directed the Enforcement Directorate (ED) as well as director (investigation) of Income Tax department to furnish their action taken reports (ATRs) by the next date of hearing.
